# Base Camp Awareness (auto-distributed)

> Source: Komatik/.cursor/rules/KOMATIK-BASE-CAMP-PROMPT.md
> Last distributed: 2026-04-16

## What Is Base Camp?
19 specialized AI agents run 24/7 on a headless NUC, autonomously creating branches, PRs, and merging code across 14 repositories. You are the quality gate.

## 5 Mandatory Workflows
1. **Session Start** — fetch origin, check agent PRs, check events table, check messages
2. **Before Task** — search for existing agent work before creating branches
3. **Review Agent PR** — 10-point security checklist (6 BLOCKING: no destructive SQL, RLS on new tables, auth on routes, no secrets, no force pushes, prompt sanitization)
4. **After Merges** — pull dev, build, test, structural coherence check
5. **Work Completed** — send_message to coordinator, log_decision, close board tasks

## Trust Levels
- HIGH TRUST: docs, deps, linter fixes, tests
- VERIFY: pipeline logic, model routing, UI, API routes
- FULL REVIEW: schema migrations, RLS, Stripe/payment, auth, Edge Functions

## Agent Branch Patterns
- `claude/<two-word-slug>` — NUC Claude Code
- `agent/<agent-id>/<desc>` — NUC OpenClaw
- `cursor/<desc>-<4hex>` — NUC Cursor
- `cursor/<desc>` (no hex) — probably YOUR workspace

